  "texts": [
    "The game also allows the child to discharge excess energy accumulated through physical activity.",
    "The game is implemented through Kinect, a tool that allows you to control game actions without the use of joypads or buttons but simply with the use of your body, thus allowing you to decode the movements made by the player without the need for any element to be connected to the body.",
    "The game is projected on a big screen, in order to allow the therapist to follow in real time the patient's performance and evaluate the progress.",
    "Two environments have been developed, depicting a country road and a city street (Fig. 2).",
    "Within the game scene, the user must run in place to move along the path, moving left or right to avoid obstacles and/or collect required objects."
